description: For APPLE CHARGER CORD Q1: Is this cable Apple mFi? A: The iPhone charger cable we sell is a MFi Lightning cable. You can log in to the official Apple MFi Accessories and search our brand "TUMABER" to confirm. Q2: Why does the phone get hot when it's charging? A: This is normal, because the phone will generate some heat when it is charging. However, the main reasons for the heat are as follows: 1. The charging speed will be faster when the phone power is low, the wall charger will output 9V high voltage, and the phone will generate heat because of the voltage converting process. 2. There are too many programs running in the background of the phone, causing the phone to run at a high load and generate more heat. Recommendations: 1. Clean up the running program of the phone with high power consumption in the background in time. 2. Don't play the phone while the phone is charged with low power, otherwise the phone will be in a high load state. Q2: Why does the phone get hot when it's charging? A: This is normal, because the phone will generate some heat when it is charging. However, the main reasons for the heat are as follows: 1. The charging speed will be faster when the phone power is low, the wall charger will output 9V high voltage, and the phone will generate heat because of the voltage converting process. 2. There are too many programs running in the background of the phone, causing the phone to run at a high load and generate more heat. Recommendations: 1. Clean up the running program of the phone with high power consumption in the background in time. 2. Don't play the phone while the phone is charged with low power, otherwise the phone will be in a high load state. About the error message "This accessory may not be supported by device": The message would appear if you were using a non-Apple wall charger or in poor transmission, but even if you are using an Apple accessory, the error can also happen for the firmware problem with iOS.

With Smart-iC Intelligent Technology, it could automatically detect your devices to deliver optimum charging speed: 1) Work with Adaptive Fast Charging (AFC) compatible devices as a fast charger; 2) Work with Quick Charge 3.0/2.0/1.0 (QC 3.0/2.0/1.0) compatible devices as a fast charger; 3) Work with other non-fast USB devices as a standard charger with normal speed. What is the difference between Quick Charge (QC) and Adaptive Fast charging (AFC)? They are basically the same technology but brands marketed in a different names. While Qualcomm named it Quick Charge, Samsung named it Adaptive Fast Charging. Should I worry that the charger gets hot while charging? This AFC technology is to quick charge your phone to 50~60 percent, then turn to the trickle mode. During charging, the charger & phone may get hot, and it will cool down after 60%. Therefore, AFC is actually not used to fully charge a device. How Fast Could It Be? This fast wall charger set compatible with both Quick Charge 3.0 and Adaptive Fast Charging (AFC), enables mobile phone to be 50% charged in 30 mins, 75% faster than conventional chargers. description: Question: Why can't the screen protector cover the entire screen? Answer: Because the screen edges of the iPhone 8, 7, 6S, 6, SE 2020 Phone models have a certain curvature, there will be a wide range of bubbles in the full-screen protector, which will affect the appearance of the phone. In response to this problem, KATIN specially designed a slightly smaller iPhone 8, 7, 6S, 6, SE 2020 screen protector, which improves the bubble problem and can be better used with mobile phone cases. Question ：Will it be difficult to install a mobile phone screen protector? Answer： Every customer who buys a product in KATIN will get an instruction manual on how to install the screen protector, which is accompanied by a very intuitive and detailed video. If you have any problems during the installation process, you can let us help you. Question ：The product is cracked or the model is wrong after receiving it? Answer：When you get a broken product, it may be caused by a large squeeze or impact during the long-term transportation. When you receive the wrong product, it may be that the warehouse receives a large amount of goods and the product is in confusion during sorting. Don't worry, Please contact Amazon service in time or get in touch with us via Amazon email following steps: Go to Your Orders, find your order in the list, and click Problem with order. and the problem will be solved well for you. Question ：Why does the edge of the screen protector break after being used for a period of time? Answer：The screen protector is made of AF explosion-proof PET and other materials after heat treatment and tempering, so the surface is hard enough, scratch-resistant, abrasion-resistant, explosion-proof, waterproof, and oil-proof, which can help your phone block daily collisions and scratches. When subjected to a severe impact, the screen protector will replace the mobile phone screen to bear all the impact and break. Within the range that Screen Protector can withstand, it can protect the phone screen from damage when dropped or hit.
